│ My previous fix was too aggressive, causing regressions in other tests. The core issue is that the `isinf` optimization in `InstCombineAndOrXor.cpp` does not correctly handle the       │
│ poison-propagating behavior of `fabs` with `nnan` and `copysign` when its second argument is poison.                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ My last attempt to fix this by unconditionally disabling the optimization for `copysign` was too broad, as the optimization is valid in some cases. The correct approach is to be more   │
│ precise.                                                                                                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The optimization is unsafe for `copysign(A, B)` if `B` can be poison. A simple, safe way to handle this is to only allow the optimization if `B` is the same value as `A`. In this case, │
│ `copysign(A, A)` is equivalent to `fabs(A)`, and we already have a check for `fabs` with `nnan`.                                                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                                          │
│ I will modify the check I added in `matchIsFiniteTest` to be more specific for `copysign`. Instead of bailing out for all `copysign` instructions, I will only bail out if the two       │
│ operands of `copysign` are different. This will allow the optimization to proceed for the safe `copysign(X, X)` case, which should fix the test regressions, while still preventing the  │
│ miscompilation.                                                                                                                                                                          │
